extends layout

block pageTitle
  title Cookie Policy — Hedge Wears

block metaDesc
  meta(name='description' content='Learn how Hedge Wears uses cookies and similar technologies on its website and web shop.')

block content

  //- ─── PAGE HERO ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  section.page-hero.section
    .container
      .page-hero-inner.page-hero-inner--centered
        span.section-eyebrow Legal
        h1.page-hero-title Cookie Policy
        p.page-hero-subtitle Last updated: May 2026

  //- ─── CONTENT ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  section.legal-page.section
    .container
      .legal-content

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 1. What Are Cookies
          p Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website. They allow the site to remember your actions and preferences over a period of time so you don&rsquo;t have to keep re-entering them each time you visit or move between pages.
          p Hedge Wears uses cookies and similar technologies (such as local storage and session tokens) on its marketing website and web shop to provide a functional, secure, and improved experience.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 2. Types of Cookies We Use
          ul
            li
              strong Strictly Necessary Cookies
              p.legal-li-desc These cookies are essential for the website and web shop to function. They enable core features such as session management, authentication, and shopping cart state. The site cannot function properly without them. These cookies do not require your consent.
            li
              strong Preference Cookies
              p.legal-li-desc These cookies remember choices you make — such as your selected display currency or notification preferences — so we can provide a personalised experience on your next visit.
            li
              strong Analytics Cookies (Anonymised)
              p.legal-li-desc We use anonymised analytics to understand how visitors use our pages — which sections are most viewed, where users navigate from, and how long sessions last. This data is aggregated and cannot be used to identify you personally.
            li
              strong Performance &amp; Error Logging
              p.legal-li-desc We collect crash reports and performance data to diagnose technical issues and improve platform stability. This data is tied to your device type and session, not to your personal identity.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 3. Third-Party Cookies
          p Some features on Hedge Wears involve third-party services that may set their own cookies:
          ul
            li
              strong Vendorstack
              |  — The commerce infrastructure powering Hedge Wears may set session and authentication cookies to enable order processing, account management, and platform functionality.
            li
              strong Paystack
              |  — Our payment processor sets cookies to maintain a secure checkout session. These are strictly necessary for payment to function. Paystack&rsquo;s cookie and privacy policy governs their use.
            li
              strong Firebase (Push Notifications)
              |  — If you have opted in to push notifications on the mobile app or web, Firebase may use device tokens and related identifiers. No browser cookies are set by Firebase on the marketing website.
          p We do not permit third parties to use cookies on Hedge Wears for advertising, retargeting, or any purpose unrelated to the delivery of our service.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 4. How Long Cookies Last
          ul
            li
              strong Session cookies
              |  — Deleted automatically when you close your browser.
            li
              strong Persistent cookies
              |  — Remain on your device for a set period (typically 30 days to 12 months) or until you manually delete them. These are used for preference storage and authentication tokens.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 5. Your Cookie Choices
          p You can control and manage cookies in the following ways:
          ul
            li
              strong Browser settings
              |  — Most browsers allow you to view, block, or delete cookies through their settings menus. Note that disabling strictly necessary cookies will break core functionality such as login and checkout.
            li
              strong Clearing cookies
              |  — You can delete all stored cookies at any time through your browser&rsquo;s history or privacy settings. This will log you out and reset any saved preferences.
            li
              strong Device settings
              |  — On mobile, you can manage app permissions (including notification access) through your device&rsquo;s Settings app.
          p Blocking or deleting cookies may affect your ability to use certain features of the Hedge Wears website or web shop, including staying signed in, saving your currency preference, and completing checkout.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 6. Changes to This Policy
          p We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in technology, legislation, or the way we operate. Any updates will be posted on this page with a revised date. Continued use of Hedge Wears after changes are published constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 7. Contact
          p If you have questions about our use of cookies, contact us at:
          p
            a.link(href='mailto:hello@hedgewears.com') hello@hedgewears.com
          p Hedge Wears, London, United Kingdom.
